<HEADLINE> Clark Backs Romania's Efforts to Join NATO and EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bucharest, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The NATO's door will remain open,
and Romania will continue to be seen as a key partner with which
the Allied Forces will develop relations, said the visiting
General Wesley Clark, the Supreme Commandant of the Allied Forces
in Europe.
</P>
<P>
Wesley Clark, who arrived here Wednesday on a two-day visit to
Romania, said that NATO military structure backs Romania's efforts
to join NATO and EU.
</P>
<P>
Describing as "warm" the discussion he had with Romanian
Foreign Minister Andrei Plesu on Thursday, Wesley Clark said to
the local press that "I am quite impressed with the considerable
progress Romania has made and I have assured Romanian Foreign
Minister I will do my best to enhance the support on behalf of the
NATO military structure to your efforts." 
</P>
